  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Polpithigama hospital closed due to fuel crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The outpatients who came to the Polpithigama Base Hospital for treatment were in a desperate situation due to the resignation of the hospital staff as the employees of the Polpithigama Co-operative Gas Station did not give fuel only to the doctors.",
        "According to a circular issued by the Minister to the hospital staff to issue fuel on a first-come, first-served basis on Friday evening and Saturday morning, a small number of hospital staff went to the petrol station to scold and insult the employees. The hospital staff said that the situation had arisen due to the doctors taking steps to prevent outpatient treatment on the morning of the 25th.",
        "Due to this situation, the patients pointed out that the entrance gate to the hospital had been closed, displaying an advertisement at the gate stating that the hospital staff had gone near the petrol station to get fuel."
      ],
